cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on image-based approaches for dietary intake assessment and introduces a semi-automatic system for online food image collection and annotation. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multimedia data (food images) and proposes a method for collecting and annotating them. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The web crawler used in the proposed system is a tool for information retrieval, specifically for downloading online food images. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The web-based crowdsourcing tool designed in the paper involves human annotators and aims to improve the efficiency of the food image annotation process. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) to some extent, as the food labels are used to retrieve relevant images using the web crawler.
